@@@ DOTNET CREATING  NEW PROJECT AND ...
===================================================================================================
      ***  to get the list(type ) of .net core projects  ===> dotnet new --list

      dotnet new classlib -n Infrastructure  
      dotnet sln add Infrastructure

      ...dotnet new classlib -n Infrastructure   then ADD ANY NEW PROJECT TO THE solution as follow ---dotnet sln add Infrastructure
      ... THEN ONCE WE ADD THE PROJECT TO THE sln   if that new project want to reference any project or referenceced by any other prokect it will do so as follow

        C:\DBA\Reactivities\Infrastructure>dotnet add reference ../Application   ie. Infrastructure need to accesse to Application project
        C:\DBA\Reactivities\API>dotnet add reference ../Infrastructure           ie. The API project need to accesse to Infrastructure project
     
And our API project is going to need access to our infrastructure projects, the classes and services are going to be needed to be added to our dependency injection container.
So we need to reference from the API to the infrastructure.
===================================================================================================


